data-triple-N3.o: "Northern Territory (abbreviated as NT) is a federal territory in the centre and central northern region of Australia. It shares borders with Western Australia to the west, South Australia to the south, and Queensland to the east. To the north, the territory is bordered by the Timor Sea, the Arafura Sea and the Gulf of Carpentaria. Despite its large areaover 1,349,129 square kilometres, making it the third largest Australian federal divisionit is sparsely populated."@en
